xxl
------------------------------------------
XXL is a library for C and C++ that provides exception handling and asset
management. Asset management is integrated with the exception handling
mechanism such that assets may be automatically cleaned up if an exception is
thrown, which allows for much simplified program structure with respect to
error handling.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.8.1-1
  libxxl-devel-1.0.1-1bl5
  libxxl1-1.0.1-1bl5
  pkg-config-0.29.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-9-1
  binutils-2.25-4
  cygport-0.24.1-1
  gcc-core-5.4.0-1
  libtool-2.4.6-4
  make-4.2.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://launchpad.net/xxl/

Canonical download:
  https://launchpad.net/xxl/1.0/1.0.1/+download/xxl-1.0.1.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack xxl-1.0.1-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./xxl-1.0.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/xxl-1.0.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/xxl-1.0.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libxxl1-1.0.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libxxl-devel-1.0.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(xxl)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/xxl.README
  /usr/share/doc/xxl/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/xxl/README

(libxxl1)
  /usr/bin/cygxxl-1.dll

(libxxl-devel)
  /usr/include/xxl.h
  /usr/lib/libxxl.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/xxl.pc
  /usr/share/doc/xxl/html/xxl.html
  /usr/share/doc/xxl/html/xxl.pdf

